                <div class="overlay">
                    <h3>Kola!, The Karnataki Culture</h3>
                    Where Warriors Dance and Spirits Soar. In the emerald embrace of Kerala's backwaters, a vibrant
                    pulse beats - the Kola culture. Here, clad in crimson and gold, transform into fierce warriors and
                    playful deities. Faces painted in stark lines, bodies adorned with jingling anklets, they become
                    conduits for ancient legends. The air thrums with the rhythm of chenda drums, a primal heartbeat urging
                    limbs to pirouette, stomp, and leap. 
                </div>
            </div>
            <br/>
            <br/>
            <div class="cult">
